# Svelte 5 Reactivity Rules

## Never pass `$derived` to external libraries that mutate data

If an external library (e.g. @xyflow/svelte, vis-timeline) needs to **write back** to the
data you pass it (positions, dimensions, selection, measured state), you **must** use
`$state.raw()` with `bind:`, never `$derived`.

`$derived` is read-only. When a library writes to it, Svelte recomputes the derived value,
which returns a new object reference (because `.map()` always creates a new array), the
library sees "new" data, processes it, writes again — infinite loop. Svelte throws
`effect_update_depth_exceeded`.

```svelte
// BAD: $derived creates read-only data; SvelteFlow writes back -> infinite loop
let nodes = $derived(computeNodes());
<SvelteFlow {nodes} />

// GOOD: $state.raw is writable; SvelteFlow can mutate positions/dimensions
let nodes = $state.raw<Node[]>([]);
$effect.pre(() => {
  someDependency;
  untrack(() => { nodes = computeNodes(); });
});
<SvelteFlow bind:nodes />
```

## Use `$state.raw()` for data passed to external libraries

Deep proxies from `$state()` cause `DataCloneError` when external libraries call
`structuredClone` internally. Use `$state.raw()` instead — it stores the value as-is
without deep proxy wrapping.

When you need to read reactive state and pass it to an external API, use
`$state.snapshot()` to strip proxies first.

## Always use `untrack()` inside `$effect` for helper calls

When an `$effect` calls functions that read reactive state internally (like
`$state.snapshot()` or store getters), wrap the body in `untrack()` and list explicit
dependencies at the top of the effect. This prevents over-broad dependency tracking.

```svelte
import { untrack } from 'svelte';

// BAD: $state.snapshot() deeply reads hundreds of reactive properties as deps
$effect(() => {
  if (!dataSet) return;
  dataSet.clear();
  dataSet.add(buildItems()); // buildItems calls $state.snapshot internally
});

// GOOD: explicit deps + untrack prevents deep implicit tracking
$effect(() => {
  campaign.filteredEvents;   // explicit dep
  campaign.data.calendar;    // explicit dep
  untrack(() => {
    if (!dataSet) return;
    dataSet.clear();
    dataSet.add(buildItems());
  });
});
```

## Minimize `$effect` usage

- **`$derived`** for pure computations (display values, filtered lists, counts)
- **Event handlers** (`onclick`, `oninput`) for user actions
- **Store callbacks** for cross-component communication (e.g. `onEditorOpen`)
- **`$effect`** only when you must sync reactive state to an imperative external library
  (vis-timeline, D3, etc.) — and always with `untrack()` + explicit deps
